    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-10-13T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-10-13T07:00:00-05:00" n="470"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d470">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.00 Revolutions/413: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at São Paulo</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_CCR1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cameron</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">São Paulo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-10-13T10:00:00-02:00"
                            >October 13, 1932—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 13—7:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Yesterday afternoon mob broke windows various stores whose proprietors considered
                    unfriendly to São Paulo. Eight killed; considerable number wounded by police
                    during rioting. All São Paulo leaders recommending peaceful attitude. No serious
                    disorders expected.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Embassy at Rio de Janeiro.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CCR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cameron</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
